==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moiety
<hw>Moi"e*ty</hw> <pr>(moi"⟦esl⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Moieties</plw>
<pr>(moi"⟦esl⟧*t⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>moiti⟦eacute⟧</ets>,
L. <ets>medietas</ets>, fr. <ets>medius</ets> middle, half. See
<er>Mid</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and cf. <er>Mediate</er>,
<er>Mediety</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of two equal parts; a
half; <as>as, a <ex>moiety</ex> of an estate, of goods, or of profits;
the <ex>moiety</ex> of a jury, or of a nation.</as></def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The more beautiful <qex>moiety</qex> of his majesty's subject.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An indefinite part; a small part.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moil</ent>⟦br⟧
